No.55/1/1/71-CF
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA(BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT(MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
Department of Cabinet Affairs(Mantrimandal Karya Vibhag)
165)
New Delhi, the 6th July, 1971.
15th Asadha, 1893.
The President has been pleased to direct that
Shri Siddhartha Shankar Ray, Minister of Education and Social
Welfare and Culture (Shiksha aur Samaj Kalyan tatha Sanskriti
Man tri) shall, until further orders, also deal with:
(a) all problems relating to West Bengal which are
within the competence of the Cen tral Government;
(b) problems created by the massive influx of refugees
from East Bengal into various States of India.
(R.N. Kalia)
for Cabinet Secretary,
To
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
